s are okay and how to configure this dynamically. Using log4j might affect static initialization, which occurs upon first use. I need to ensure that branches for log4j are correctly set up to avoid issues with FrameworkLogger accessibility.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating log4j dependencies**\\n\\nI need to add dependencies for log4j2. I'm wondering if log4j-core is necessary or if I can just use log4j-api. FrameworkLogger checks for Logger and LogManager, and without core, it seems log4j-api would use SimpleLogger as a fallback. I should verify the version compatibility, particularly with HSQLDB 2.4.1. If I'm using log4j-api 2.17, it likely has the logging interfaces I need, including relevant methods and dynamic class loading capabilities, for proper functionality.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating logging dependencies**\\n\\nI’m considering the logging dependencies here. There's the question about using log4j-api alone, and whether I can swap in log4j 1.2.17 instead. HSQLDB seems to prefer version 2 first, but will fall back to version 1 if needed. Using log4j 1.2.17 might help reduce native issues, though it’s older and might not support transitive dependencies. I need to ask whether it includes the right metadata for the dependencies or just for the direct ones when testing.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_5RWI1D4qAdFFOBb1B0CpWzrR|fc_0578e49ef16e66dc0169f90a9c0d1c8192a69dfea3df2a38ad", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg -n '\"type\"\\s*:\\s*\"org.apache.log4j.(Level|Logger|Priority)\"|toLevel|getLogger|\"name\"\\s*:\\s*\"log\"' metadata/log4j/log4j/1.2.17/reachability-metadata.json -C 2"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 612, "output": 1755, "cacheRead": 23040, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 25407, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777928837092, "responseId": "r